If your `test-v1.sh` expects specific output formats (e.g., standard git output), adjust the `println!` statements in `main.rs` to match the exact string requirements of your specification. If the spec requires `commit` functionality, you would extend `main.rs` to create a file in `.minigit/refs` pointing to the latest object hash.
